An unusually open and unique image of Karel Gott in the feature-length documentary film by Olga Špátová
This unique film from the workshop of Olga Špátová will premiere in Czech cinemas in the spring of next year.
&quot;In the middle of September last year, Ivanka and Karel Gott called me and asked me if I would make a documentary about his life with Karel again after ten years. I didn&#39;t hesitate for a minute! Filming with a person who has lasted more than half a century at the forefront of Czech culture thanks to his exceptional singing talent, artistic humility and immeasurable hard work, it was and is a great honor for me. I accepted the challenge to make a feature-length documentary film about Karl Gott, who has brought joy to three generations of listeners with his art, as a commitment to this legendary singer, &quot; director Olga Špátová describes her feelings.
