Trump is considering delisting Chinese stocks in the US
The administration of US President Donald Trump is considering revoking the permission of Chinese companies to trade on stock markets in the United States. An informed source told Reuters today. Such a move would be a radical escalation of trade tensions between the US and China. Shares of the companies concerned on the New York Stock Exchange immediately headed down after the news, dragging the entire market down with it.
